a:3:{s:4:"time";i:1642984046;s:3:"ttl";i:3600;s:4:"data";a:2:{s:4:"list";a:3:{i:0;a:62:{s:5:"wr_id";s:2:"42";s:6:"wr_num";s:3:"-40";s:8:"wr_reply";s:0:"";s:9:"wr_parent";s:2:"42";s:13:"wr_is_comment";s:1:"0";s:10:"wr_comment";s:1:"0";s:16:"wr_comment_reply";s:0:"";s:7:"ca_name";s:0:"";s:9:"wr_option";s:5:"html1";s:10:"wr_subject";s:47:"ISO 14064 Greenhouse Gas Emissions and Removals";s:10:"wr_content";s:13269:"<div style="text-align:justify;">

<p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="    background-color: rgb(217, 238, 236);"><b>[ISO 14064 Introduction]</b></span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">An increasing number of organizations are voluntarily monitoring and reporting greenhouse gas emissions and managing carbon emissions more efficiently.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">ISO 14064 provides a framework for estimating and verifying greenhouse gas emissions for organizations seeking to quantify and reduce their greenhouse gas emissions.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">Part 1 - Organization-level guidance for the quantification and reporting of greenhouse gas emissions and removals.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">It specifies organizational-level principles and requirements for the quantification and reporting of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions and removals.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">This includes requirements for the design, development, management, reporting and validation of an organization's GHG inventory.</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">Part 2 - Project-level guidance for the quantification, monitoring, and reporting of improvements in greenhouse gas emissions reduction or elimination.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">It specifies principles and requirements and provides project-level guidance for the quantification, monitoring, and reporting of activities that seek to increase reduction or elimination of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">This includes requirements for GHG project planning, identification, and selection of GHG sources, sinks and reservoirs (SSRs) related to the project and baseline scenarios, monitoring, quantification, documentation and reporting of GHG project performance, and data quality management.</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">Part 3 - Guidelines for validation and verification of greenhouse gas statements.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">It specifies principles and requirements and provides guidance for verifying and validating greenhouse gas (GHG) statements. Applies to organizations, projects, and products GHG statements.</span></p><p><br></p><div style="text-align: center;" align="center">


<div style="text-align:center;width:60%;margin:0% 20%;" align="center"><img src="https://www.igcert.org/igc_eng/data/editor/2201/bdeca81661f9ce9da23d762ae08f5293_1641345453_2185.jpg" title="bdeca81661f9ce9da23d762ae08f5293_1641345453_2185.jpg" alt="ISO 14064 Greenhouse Gas Emissions and Removals"></div>


</div>&nbsp;<p><br></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="    background-color: rgb(217, 238, 236);"><b>[Importance of ISO 14064 Certification]</b></span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">1. GHG risk management and identification of opportunities for reduction A company can establish a comprehensive GHG inventory to understand the company's GHG emissions status, responsibilities, and risks.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">At the same time, it can help businesses find the most cost-effective reduction opportunities through estimating and accounting of their greenhouse gas emissions.</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">2. Improve energy and material efficiency and reduce operating costs. By developing new products and services, you can reduce the greenhouse gas emissions of your customers or suppliers.</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">3. Building a Good Image of Social Responsibility</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">With growing interest in climate change, more and more non-governmental organizations, investors, or other stakeholders are asking businesses to disclose more information about their greenhouse gas emissions. Disclosure of a company's GHG emissions information can strengthen good relationships with stakeholders and build a corporate image of 'social responsibility and environmental management' to customers and the public.</span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">4. Participate in the Greenhouse Gas Emission Trading Market</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">In recent years, some regions have begun to implement methods using market mechanisms to offset greenhouse gas emissions. These trading plans require more realistic emissions and set emission targets or caps to decide whether to buy or sell allowances, and usually only require direct emission estimates. At the same time, to support independent inspections, these emission trading systems require participating companies to establish traceability for verification of reported greenhouse gas information.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="    background-color: rgb(217, 238, 236);"><b>[Scope of ISO 14064]</b></span></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">1. Enterprise risk management: identifying and managing opportunities and risks, etc.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">2. Voluntary Actions: Activities such as participating in voluntary GHG registration or reporting actions.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">3. GHG Markets: Buying and selling of GHG quotas and credits</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">4. Laws and regulations or government departments require reporting such as obtaining credit lines due to proactive measures, negotiated contracts, or national reporting systems.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="   ">If have any other or related inquiries, please contact us using the contact information below.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.8;"><span style="    color: rgb(0, 117, 200);">E-mail: info@igcert.org&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p>

</div>


